Is Listening to a Book Just as Good as Reading It?

Do you listen to audiobooks? What are the benefits, in your opinion, of listening instead of reading? Are there advantages to reading that cannot be gained by listening? Which method do you prefer? Why?

---

In my opinion,

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: For fiction, however, listening is a poor substitute for reading.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The reason for this is that the experience of reading a book is not just about absorbing the information.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The reader is transported to the world of the book, and the reader is able to experience the world of the book in a way that is not possible

actions.name: text-insert

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: I don't want to hear the author's voice, I want to hear the narrator's.
